@subsubsection rd_multiprotocol_support_implemented_sd_arbiter_1 Time-multiplexed radio access

Time-multiplexed radio access is achieved by utilizing a radio arbiter.
The nRF IEEE 802.15.4 radio driver manages its radio transactions through radio arbiter and requests timeslots prior to any radio activity.

