@section rd_multiprotocol_support_hf_clock Handling high-frequency clock

When the RADIO peripheral is used, the Radio Scheduler module makes sure that the high-frequency clock (HFCLK) is running before starting the radio procedures.

Note that the 802.15.4 driver uses the nrf_drv_clock driver to request or release the high-frequency clock (HFCLK).
Any other radio stacks or modules (like NFC) should also use nrf_drv_clock to ensure HFCLK is not accidentally stopped within the radio activity of the nRF IEEE 802.15.4 radio driver.

